data-triple-N3.o: "A chemical formula is a way of expressing information about the proportions of atoms that constitute a particular chemical compound, using a single line of chemical element symbols, numbers, and sometimes also other symbols, such as parentheses, dashes, brackets, and plus (+) and minus () signs. These are limited to a single typographic line of symbols, which may include subscripts and superscripts. A chemical formula contains no words."@en
